Step 1. Calculate Operating Cash Flow Ratio  
• Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Operating CF / Total Current Liabilities  
Operating CF = –81,548.37  
Total Current Liabilities = 728,279.50  
Ratio = –81,548.37 / 728,279.50 ≈ –0.112 → –0.11

Step 2. Calculate Cash Flow to Debt Ratio  
• Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = Operating CF / Total Debt  
Total Debt is taken as total liabilities. Here it is 728,279.50  
Ratio = –81,548.37 / 728,279.50 ≈ –0.112 → –0.11

Step 3. Calculate Inventory Turnover Ratio  
• Inventory Turnover Ratio = Cost of Goods Sold / Average Inventory  
Cost of Goods Sold = 3,020,000.00  
Inventory: Since initial inventory is 0 and end inventory is 440,000.00,  
Average Inventory = (0 + 440,000.00) / 2 = 220,000.00  
Ratio = 3,020,000.00 / 220,000.00 ≈ 13.73

Step 4. Calculate Debt to Equity Ratio  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Debt / Total Owner's Equity  
Total Debt = 728,279.50  
Total Owner’s Equity (end) = 14,095,371.35  
Ratio = 728,279.50 / 14,095,371.35 ≈ 0.0517 → 0.05

Step 5. Calculate Quick Ratio  
• Quick Ratio = (Current Assets – Inventory) / Current Liabilities  
Current Assets = 9,193,203.41  
Less Inventory = 440,000.00  
Quick Assets = 9,193,203.41 – 440,000.00 = 8,753,203.41  
Quick Ratio = 8,753,203.41 / 728,279.50 ≈ 12.02

Step 6. Calculate Current Ratio  
• Current Ratio = Current Assets / Current Liabilities  
Current Ratio = 9,193,203.41 / 728,279.50 ≈ 12.62

Thus, our final solution is:

    "Inventory Turnover Ratio": "13.73",

    "Quick Ratio": "12.02",
    "Current Ratio": "12.62"
  }
}
